    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-19T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="866"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.48/1050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Vice
                        Consul at Viborg</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Imbrie</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-19T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1919—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your 165, December 15th. Department believes Viborg stores should be sent to
                    Reval at once for relief <persName corresp="#p_YGNN1">Yudenitch</persName> army
                    and refugees or such other port as <persName corresp="#p_GJA1">Gade</persName>
                    may deem best in view of possible Bolshevik advance.</p>
                <p>Your 167, 16th,<note n="82" xml:id="d866fn82">Not printed.</note> repeated to
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJA1">Gade</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
